channel.title: Homerton and Milltown insects
channel.description: Flora and fauna in one of the 10' (minute) grids in the Victorian Biodiversity Atlas called E05. It is about 14 km long by 10 km wide and includes sections of the Darlot Creek, the Fitzroy River and Lake Condah, stony rises, heathy woodland, state forests and Mt Eccles National Park as well as roadside vegetation. The study started in about 2008 and is ongoing.
